<p>HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL 
Sixth session 
Agenda item 10 
</p>
<p><b>TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE AND CAPACITY-BUILDING 
</b></p>
<p><b>Egypt (on behalf of the African Group):  Amendments to  
draft resolution A/HRC/6/L.40 
</b></p>
<p><b>6/&#8230; Mandate of the Special Rapporteur on the  
situation of human rights in the Sudan 
</b></p>
<p>1. Delete the fifth, eighth and ninth preambular paragraphs. 
</p>
<p>2. Replace operative paragraph 1 by: 
</p>
<p> 1. <i>Decides</i> to defer the decision pertaining to the review, rationalization and 
improvement of the mandate of the Special Rapporteur on the situation of human rights in 
the Sudan to the eighth session of the Council in June 2008; 
</p>
<p>3. After paragraph 1, insert the following new paragraph: 
</p>
<p> 2. <i>Requests</i> the Special Rapporteur to engage in an open and constructive 
dialogue with the Government of the Sudan in fulfilling her mandate and to cooperate with 
the Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights and the relevant 
United Nations mechanisms, taking into account the relevant resolutions and reports, 
inter alia, the final report on the situation of human rights in Darfur prepared by the group 
of experts (A/HRC/6/19); 
</p>
<p>4. Renumber the subsequent paragraphs accordingly. 
</p>
